description: Recently sold: $371,880. Welcome to our newest one level floor plan in this great development of Northpointe with-in the Centennial School District! This lovely home includes 3 bedrooms, 2 full baths, custom open kitchen with center island and granite countertops, living room, owners suite with large walk-in closet and full owners bath, 2 more generous sized bedrooms, full main bath and main floor laundry room. This home is a must see!

Recently sold: $225,000. Meticulous former model loaded w/upgrades.  Remodeled kitchen with large granite countertops and all new high-end stainless steel LG appliances.  Kitchen cabinets are newly painted gray with a built in wine rack for entertaining.  The millwork under the peninsula is painted white. Refinished hardwood floors in a dark antique oak stain lend a modern look to the first level. End unit-streaming w/natural light! 6 panel doors, deluxe surround sound system w/wall & ceiling speakers & finished garage with speakers.  The wood trim throughout the first level has all been newly painted white to give it a fresh new look. New brushed nickel door hardware throughout the house gives a fresh look.  Open gas fireplace between the living room and dining room.  3 bedrooms on 1 level. Travertine and marble floor in the master bath compliment the granite vanity top. Unique bathroom and kitchen light fixtures give an artsy, modern feel to the home. New powder room cabinet and copper bowl with waterfall faucet give a chabby chic appearance.  High end, 100% nylon carpet in lower level. Hunter Douglas ceiling fans in every room along with Hunter Douglas white wood horizontal blinds and Hunter Douglas Luminette Vertical Blinds in the dining room.  Completely insulated garage, including the door and a new  Chamberlain Lift Master Ultra Quiet Belt Driven opener. description: Recently sold: $185,000.

Recently sold: $195,000. Spacious 2 bedroom, 2 bath town home in pretty Water's Edge. Living room with gas fireplace, dining room + breakfast nook, covered deck off the kitchen for grilling, laundry room and 1/2 bath on the main level. Upstairs are 2 bedrooms, loft area and a full bath that walks through to the master. The walk out level has a flex room, currently it is an office but it could be a family or play room. Community clubhouse with a fitness center with locker room, sports court, playground, outdoor pool and children's pools and a party room for gatherings.  Sidewalks wind through the development so can walk to clubhouse or hop on the walking/biking trail along Oneka Parkway. Parking is such a common issue with town home developments, not here, there is guest parking directly across from the front door.  Close to shopping and restaurants with easy access to 35E and Highway 61.  Just a few minutes north of Bald Eagle and White Bear Lakes and charming downtown White Bear Lake, you'll love living here.
